It is Religion, that holdeth vs at a bay, and keepeth the heart of the Subiect in awe, that it swelleth not against the Soueraigne. Wherefore it shall be requisite for a well disposed Prince, in time of Peace, to prouide for that which shall preserue his Peace; to giue his loue and life vnto Diuinitie, whereby his heart may alwayes be in the hand of God; as that holy man Athanasius sayd to the Emperour Iouinian;
               Theod. lib. 4. Cap. 3.
               Conueniens est pro Principe studium et amor diuinarum rerum; nam sic habebis semper cor tuum in manu Domini: The studie and loue of Heauenly things, is most conuenient for a godly Prince; for so thou shalt haue alwayes thine heart in the hand of God.

After the death of King Salomon, Sesack King of Egipt spoyled the Temple which was at
• erusalem, 1. King. 14. or Ses • stris, as Josephus would haue it, or Smendes as others doe conceiue;
which of them soeuer it was, he that fared best, bought it deare enough: The Thracians inuading and subduing to themselues the Dominions of the one; the other dying, left his heire behind him in this case most miserable, that for a long season he was smitten with blindnesse.
